        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(google): bound Veo video operation response reads",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThis bounds **only** the Google **Veo video** REST fallback operation read in `extensions/google/video-generation-provider.ts` (`requestGoogleVideoJson`), which used an unbounded `await response.text()` before checking `response.ok`. The Veo create/poll operation response is external provider content; a hostile or misconfigured endpoint can stream an arbitrarily large body that is fully buffered into memory — a memory-pressure / hang (OOM) vector. (Scope is the video-generation operation JSON only — distinct from #96324, which covers Google embedding/image/media/oauth/speech and does not touch `video-generation-provider.ts`.)\n\n## Evidence\n\nReuses the shared bounded reader `readResponseWithLimit` (16 MiB cap, cancels the stream on overflow) — same pattern as the recently merged #95218 / #96027 / #96038. Plugin-scoped; the `response.ok` / HTTP-detail / success `JSON.parse` flow is otherwise unchanged. create and poll share `requestGoogleVideoJson`, so both paths are covered.\n\nReal behavior proof (live vitest, not mocked): a real `ReadableStream` streaming a 64 MiB body is fed to the exported request path, asserting `Google video operation response exceeds 16777216 bytes` is thrown, `wasCanceled() === true`, `getReadCount() < 64`.\n\n```\nTests  16 passed (16)\n```\n",
        "branch": "fix/bound-google-video",
